-- Real Madrid Defeats Granada 5-1 to Extend Spanish Soccer Lead
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-01-07T21:58:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-07/real-madrid-defeats-granada-5-1-to-extend-spanish-soccer-lead.html
Real Madrid beat Granada 5-1 to
increase its lead over Barcelona in Spanish soccer’s Primera
Liga.  Karim Benzema had two goals and Sergio Ramos,  Gonzalo Higuain  and  Cristiano Ronaldo  scored once each at Madrid’s
Bernabeu Stadium. Real moves six points ahead of Barcelona,
which plays Espanyol tomorrow.  Diego Milito scored twice in the first half to help Inter
Milan to 5-0 home win over Parma in Italy’s Serie A.  Thiago Motta, Giampaolo Pazzini and Marco Davide Faroni
also scored as Inter moved up to fifth place, five points behind
co-leaders AC Milan and Juventus, which both play tomorrow.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
